What do you read when you feel down?
Adam Taha
I am passionate about writing · Author has 5K answers and 95.6M answer views · 6y ·

1. The Dog Solution Tweets
I like animals and they are dogs and cats. So when I’m feeling a bit rough then I check out the dog solution, The photos of the dogs put a smile on my face because they can turn anything what we take for granted into awesomeness…

Check out Dog Solution (@DogSolutions) | Twitter

2. Fake Science Tweets
Now I didn’t excel much in science when at school but still, I enjoy science with a Parody twist. So if your’e into science and want to roll your eyes, smile or laugh then Fake Science will do it for you…

Check it out at Fake Science (@FakeScience) | Twitter

3. HitchHikers Guide to the Galaxy
It’s about the adventures of Arthur Dent, a hapless Englishman, who learns the Earth is going to be demolished to make way for a galactic freeway He is then taken or more preciselt plunked from planet earth and what happens next is one cracking awesome adventure.

I like reading this book over and over again…

4. Your illustrated Guide to the Universe
 Far in the universe is a silent voice and yet ever so powerful, a world filled beings, worlds and most of all…you. This book takes you on a lessons and it’s not some self development book but rather leads you on a journey with gorgeous illustrations to become one…with the universe.
